                                "stop": 9.205,
                                "byte_start": 105472,
                                "byte_stop": 142357,
                                "text": "Justice Breyer has our opinion this morning in case 08-1107 Hertz Corporation versus Friend."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 9.205,
                        "stop": 194.246,
                        "byte_start": 142357,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15139,
                            "name": "Stephen G. Breyer",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/stephen_g_breyer",
                            "last_name": "Breyer",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2785,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 775890000,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": "Bill Clinton",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2785"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32682,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 49908,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/stephen_g_breyer_0.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 7777,
                            "identifier": "stephen_g_breyer"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 9.205,
                                "stop": 17.748,
                                "byte_start": 142357,
                                "byte_stop": 176525,
                                "text": "The Constitution provides that federal courts may hear controversies between citizens of different states."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 17.748,
                                "stop": 29.346,
                                "byte_start": 176525,
                                "byte_stop": 222919,
                                "text": "Let\u2019s supposed the citizen of Nebraska brings a federal diversity case in Federal Court against the corporation that does some business in Nebraska, and some business elsewhere."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 29.346,
                                "stop": 37.757,
                                "byte_start": 222919,
                                "byte_stop": 256564,
                                "text": "Is the corporation a citizen of Nebraska, same state so they couldn\u2019t bring it or of a different state in which case they could?"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 37.757,
                                "stop": 59.104,
                                "byte_start": 256564,
                                "byte_stop": 341932,
                                "text": "A congressional statute answers this question by stating that, \u201ca corporation shall be deemed to a citizen of any State by which it has been incorporated and of the State where it has its principal place of business\u201d that helps, but what does principal place of business mean?"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 59.104,
                                "stop": 67.143,
                                "byte_start": 341932,
                                "byte_stop": 374115,
                                "text": "Lower courts have reached different conclusions, taking highly divergent approaches to the interpretive problem."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 67.143,
                                "stop": 95.06,
                                "byte_start": 374115,
                                "byte_stop": 485815,
                                "text": "One major treaty for example devotes 73 pages to describing a host of different tests used in different circuits, with some circuits emphasizing the locus of operations, others, the corporate nerve center and still others working with various combinations of plant size, service or sales centers, employment and other factors designed to locate a center of gravity."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 95.06,
                                "stop": 105.217,
                                "byte_start": 485815,
                                "byte_stop": 526357,
                                "text": "Ultimately, we conclude that the phrase \u201cprincipal place of business\u201d refers to what some lower courts have called the corporation\u0027s nerve center."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 105.217,
                                "stop": 112.596,
                                "byte_start": 526357,
                                "byte_stop": 555928,
                                "text": "The place where a corporation\u0027s officers direct, control and coordinate the corporations activities."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 112.596,
                                "stop": 117.174,
                                "byte_start": 555928,
                                "byte_stop": 574213,
                                "text": "Typically, the nerve center will be found at a corporation\u0027s headquarters."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 117.174,
                                "stop": 122.718,
                                "byte_start": 574213,
                                "byte_stop": 596365,
                                "text": "Our opinion sets forth our reasons for reaching this conclusion in some detail."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 122.718,
                                "stop": 137.149,
                                "byte_start": 596365,
                                "byte_stop": 654148,
                                "text": "They include our reliance upon the statute language, for example, the phrase \u201cprincipal place of business\u201d that word place is singular not plural and the word principal requires us to pick out the main, prominent or leading place."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 137.149,
                                "stop": 143.89,
                                "byte_start": 654148,
                                "byte_stop": 681106,
                                "text": "But we also place considerable weight upon the practical need for administrative simplicity."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 143.89,
                                "stop": 157.255,
                                "byte_start": 681106,
                                "byte_stop": 734501,
                                "text": "Many of the lower court tests complicate the case, eating up time and money as the parties litigate not the merits of their claims but which court is the right court to decide those merits."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 157.255,
                                "stop": 169.826,
                                "byte_start": 734501,
                                "byte_stop": 784865,
                                "text": "We\u2019ve recognized that there maybe no perfect test that satisfies all administrative and purposive criteria, but we believe a nerve center approach will point courts in the right direction."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 169.826,
                                "stop": 176.542,
                                "byte_start": 784865,
                                "byte_stop": 811719,
                                "text": "It will provide a test that is easier to apply most of the time perhaps not all the time."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 176.542,
                                "stop": 187.781,
                                "byte_start": 811719,
                                "byte_stop": 856649,
                                "text": "Though it will indeed sometimes produce counterintuitive results because the Ninth Circuit approached the jurisdictional problem before us differ."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 187.781,
                                "stop": 192.074,
                                "byte_start": 856649,
                                "byte_stop": 873785,
                                "text": "We vacate its judgment and we remand the case for further proceedings."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 192.074,
                                "stop": 194.246,
                                "byte_start": 873785,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Our decision is unanimous."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
